{"title": "Leakage of sensitive data in local storage", "summary": "  Sensitive data should not be stored in a `localStorage` session. This policy looks for any sensitive data stored within the localstorage. ", "description": "\n\nSensitive data should not be stored in a `localStorage` session. This policy looks for any sensitive data stored within the localstorage.\n", "recommendations": "\n\nIt's best to avoid storing sensitive data in `localStorage` whenever possible. To keep session data safe, use a server-based session storage solution instead.\n\n\u274c If you do need do store data in `localStorage`, avoid including sensitive data:\n\n```javascript\nlocalStorage.setItem('user', email)\n```\n\n\u2705 Instead, use a unique identifier:\n\n```javascript\nlocalStorage.setItem('user', user.uuid)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-312"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_session", "https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A3_2017-Sensitive_Data_Exposure"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}